The paper proposes a method for disentangling using both labeled and unlabeled data, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of unsupervised or weakly supervised learning. The method is applied to image datasets, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. The use of autoencoder structures and encoding-swap-decoding process suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the importance of interpretable disentangled representations, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
